[@covered by the epidermis, blackish brown. Teliospores ellipsoid, ovoid, oblong,
22–30 × 14–18 µm, at apex with a ﬂat hyaline papilla, wall smooth, brown,
≤ 7 µm thick at apex, pedicel deciduous, brownish.#Description*]
[@Known from Asia and Europe, U. veratri is a new rust species for Turkey.#Misc-exposition*]
[@Specimen examined – On Veratrum album L. (Melanthiaceae). TURKEY: Ardahan,
Posof, Ilgar mountain pass, 2540 m, 26.08.2009, Sanli Kabaktepe 7023 (INU 8548).#Misc-exposition*]
